'''if statement  = block of code that will be executed if the condition is true.
 else statement = block of code which will be executed when if statements condition fails.
it is not necessary to write a else block . but for witinf a else block it is compulsory to write a if statement.'''

age=int(input("Enter your age: "))

if age>=18:
    print("You  are eligible to vote")
    
else:
    print("You are not eligible to vote")
